<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc41a35f7-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7808"><num value="7808">§ 7808.</num><heading> Service to be independent unit</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">It is the purpose of this chapter that, under control and supervision of the Secretary, the Service shall function as an independent unit in the Department and shall have exclusive control over all its activities including sales, procurement and supply, finance, including disbursements, and personnel management, except as otherwise provided in this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc41a35f8-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/857">Pub. L. 85–857</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1250">72 Stat. 1250</ref>, § 4208; <ref href="/us/pl/97/295/s4/90">Pub. L. 97–295, § 4(90)</ref>, <date date="1982-10-12">Oct. 12, 1982</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/1312">96 Stat. 1312</ref>; renumbered § 7808 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/40/tIV/s402/a">Pub. L. 102–40, title IV, § 402(a)</ref>, (b)(1), <date date="1991-05-07">May 7, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/238">105 Stat. 238</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s4/a/3">Pub. L. 102–83, § 4(a)(3)</ref>, (4), (b)(1), (2)(E), <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/404">105 Stat. 404</ref>, 405.)</sourceCredit>
